  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "A mutiny.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And it came to the ears of the committee, and they went to talk to these boys.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They were maybe 18-, 19-, 20-year-olds.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "What will you do with a ship if you do this?",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "You don't know anything about handling a ship or sailing a ship or anything else.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And they-- they-- they were able to discourage them from pursuing this idea.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And so there were patrols organized 24 hours a day from among the young men to make sure that everybody was safe, and so on and so forth.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "The telegrams kept coming and going, and as we neared Germany, there is telegram in my father's handwriting to the Hamburg America line, which is the company to which the ship belonged, the [INAUDIBLE], asking them to substitute another ship for us to transfer us onto another ship, but not to let us come back to Germany.",
      "word_count": 57
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "In other words, if the has to go back to its cruising schedule, bring us-- get us on another ship.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Meanwhile, the captain had confided in my father that if nothing else, he would take the off the coast of Sussex and set it on fire.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "He didn't-- he felt the way he was planning to do it, nobody would be endangered and the British would be forced to take us in.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And he writes this in a little book that he himself wrote about the trip with the that that was his intention.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Because he felt it was his duty, it was his job, to deliver passengers to where they wanted to go.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "The captain was very much in sympathy to us.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "He was very cooperative.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And again, he was on the bad list of the gestapo.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
